    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>floured cheese mixture </strong>to the pan with your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Bring to a boil over a medium heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 2-3 min, stirring frequently, or until the cheese has melted and thickened – this is your <strong>triple cheese fondue</strong></p>",
